4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT PROVIDING FOR THE CRIME OF ASSAULT ON AN EMPLOYEE
5 OF A PUBLIC UTILITY OR ELECTRIC COOPERATIVE; AND PROVIDING PENALTIES.
6
7 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
8
9 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Assault on employee of public utility or electric cooperative. (1) A
10 person commits the offense of assault on an employee of a public utility, as defined in 69-3-101, or electric
11 cooperative, as defined in 35-18-102, if the person purposely or knowingly causes:
12 (a) bodily injury to an employee of a public utility or electric cooperative;
13 (b) reasonable apprehension of serious bodily injury in an employee of a public utility or electric
14 cooperative by use of:
15 (i) a weapon; or
16 (ii) what reasonably appears to be a weapon;
17 (c) bodily injury to an employee of a public utility or electric cooperative with a weapon; or
18 (d) serious bodily injury to an employee of a public utility or electric cooperative.
19 (2) (a) A person convicted of assault on an employee of a public utility or electric cooperative:
20 (i) under subsection (1)(a), (1)(b)(i), or (1)(c) shall be imprisoned in the state prison for a term not
21 to exceed 10 years and may be fined an amount not to exceed $50,000; or
22 (ii) under subsection (1)(b)(ii) shall be imprisoned in the state prison for a term not to exceed 8
23 years and may be fined an amount not to exceed $50,000.
24 (b) Except as provided in 46-18-222, a person convicted of assault on an employee of a public
25 utility or electric cooperative under subsection (1)(d) of this section shall be fined an amount not to exceed
26 $50,000 or be imprisoned in the state prison for a term not to exceed 20 years, or both.
